## 🐛 Bug Report

Parse big csv file/stream slowly. 

Lib version:4.4.0

## Steps To Reproduce


```javascript

const Excel = require("exceljs");
async function  test(params) {
    ...
    const workbook = new Excel.Workbook();
    const worksheet = await workbook.csv.read(stream);  //this line take a very long time  about 10 mins
    ....
}
test()

```



## using fast-csv directly:

```javascript
const csv = require('fast-csv')

fs.createReadStream(`xxx`)
  .pipe(csv.parse({}))
  .on('data', function (row) {
    data.push(row)
  })
  .on('end', function () {
    console.log('Data loaded',data.length)
  })

```
A same csv file using fast-csv directly only take about 5 secs
